String->String

utility class

- join(CharSequence delimiter, CharSequence... elems)
    - returns a new String that is composed of the elems separated by delimiter
- join(CharSequence delimiter, Iterable<CharSequence> elements)
- valueOf(int i) returns string representation of i
    - also for: char, double, float, boolean, char[], Object
- format(Locale locale, String format, Object... args) returns formatted string
    - locale: optional
    - format specifiers
        - %c: char
        - %d: integer
        - %f: floating point
        - %n: line separator
        - %s: string
        - %x: hex
    - alternatively: System.out.printf()

- SEE ALSO
    - javatpoint.com/java-string-format
